{
  "stem": "15721.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I still see myself and against the door and went out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that was the one time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he had already been chancellor.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, this was after '33 that I was in the same room with him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Having been a veteran, he had been a sergeant in the army, he was at Verdun, that French fortress, for four and a half years.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Over half a million soldiers died and over a million casualties for a total gain of about 100 yards of-- of territory.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] He looked very Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "By the way, people judged that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He always called himself, he said, I look like a whole synagogue.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But my father would go into a street car after the Nazis came and would take out the Jewish newspaper and open it up.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was so scared I would go out into the vestibule, ready to jump if anybody did anything to him.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I-- I wouldn't even sit next to my father because I was so embarrassed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But this little Jew, he was smaller than I and I'm not tall, would be that feisty.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But that was my old man.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He just did it that way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as I might tell you later, I had the opportunity and was finally selected for a scholarship to go to the United States to pursue my rabbinic training in Cincinnati at the Hebrew Union College in 1935.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In 1937, which was the time that my youngest brother was to be bar mitzvah, and fulfilling a promise I had given my parents that I would only be gone two years, I came back to Germany in 1937, in the summer.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
